<i>noun</i>: 손상 [손ː상], 상해 [상해], 상처 [상처], 부상 [부ː상], 관통상 [관ː통상] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>손상 [손ː상]</dt><br>
<dd>1. damage; harm; impairment</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 물건이 깨지거나 상함.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which a certain object has been broken or harmed.</dd><br>
<dd>2. injury</dd><br>
<dd>병이 들거나 몸의 일부분이 다침.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which someone is sick or a part of his/her body has been hurt.</dd><br>
<dd>3. deterioration; impairment</dd><br>
<dd>품질이 나빠짐.</dd><br>
<dd>The worsening of the quality of something.</dd><br>
<dd>4. degradation; injury</dd><br>
<dd>명예나 체면, 가치 등이 떨어짐.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which one's honor, dignity, value, etc., has been damaged.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>상해 [상해]</dt><br>
<dd>injury; wound</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람의 몸에 상처를 내어 해를 끼침.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of doing harm to another person's body by injuring it.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>상처 [상처]</dt><br>
<dd>1. wound; scar; injury</dd><br>
<dd>몸을 다쳐서 상한 자리.</dd><br>
<dd>Cuts and bruises caused by being injured.</dd><br>
<dd>2. wound; scar</dd><br>
<dd>피해를 당해 마음이 아픈 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of being heartbroken due to the suffering of loss.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>부상 [부ː상]</dt><br>
<dd>injury</dd><br>
<dd>몸에 상처를 입음.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of having an injury to the body.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>관통상 [관ː통상]</dt><br>
<dd>wound; injury</dd><br>
<dd>총알이나 칼 등이 몸을 꿰뚫어 생긴 상처.</dd><br>
<dd>An injury from a bullet, knife, etc., that has pierced the body.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>